# Module Hierarchy

```text
CPU_TOP
│
├── Clock Divider
├── Program Loader
├── Control Unit (FSM)
│
├── Program Counter (PC)
├── Memory Address Register (MAR)
├── RAM (16×8)
├── Instruction Register (IR)
│
├── A Register
├── B Register
├── ALU
├── Flag Register
├── Output Register
│
├── Input Interface
│
└── Seven Segment Driver
```

## Module Description

### Clock Divider

Generates slow and fast clocks for CPU execution.

### Program Loader

Automatically loads demo programs into RAM.

### Control Unit (FSM)

Controls instruction fetch, decode, execute, wait-input and halt operations.

### Program Counter (PC)

Stores the address of the next instruction.

### Memory Address Register (MAR)

Stores the RAM address during memory operations.

### RAM

Stores program instructions and user data.

### Instruction Register (IR)

Stores the currently executing instruction.

### A Register

Stores the primary operand and ALU result.

### B Register

Stores the secondary operand.

### ALU

Performs arithmetic and logical operations.

Supported Operations:

* ADD
* SUB
* MUL
* INC
* DEC
* CLR
* SWP

### Flag Register

Stores processor status flags:

* Zero Flag (Z)
* Carry Flag (C)

### Output Register

Stores final output before display.

### Input Interface

Handles switch inputs, sensor inputs and user interaction.

### Seven Segment Driver

Drives the 8 seven-segment displays.

Display Allocation:

HEX7 HEX6 → Program Counter (PC)

HEX5 HEX4 → Instruction Register (IR)

HEX3 HEX2 → A Register

HEX1 HEX0 → Output Register

